HashMap:

HashMap.put(key, value): Inserts a key-value pair into the HashMap.

HashMap.remove(key): removes a key-value pair from the HashMap if it present.
If the map contains the specified key, the mapping associated with that key is removed from the map, and the removed value is returned.
If the map does not contain the specified key, the method simply returns null, indicating that there was no mapping for that key.

HashMap.get(key): Returns the value associated with the specified key.

HashMap.containsKey(key): Checks if the HashMap contains the specified key.

HashMap.containsValue(val): Checks if the HashMap contains the specified value.

HashMap.size(): Returns the number of key-value mappings in the HashMap.

Set<Object> keys = map.keySet() : This method returns a Set view of the keys contained in this map.

Collection<Object> values = map.values(): This method returns a Collection view of the values contained in this map.
we can use it as: for (Object value : values) {}

Set<Map.Entry<Object, Object>> entries = map.entrySet(): This method returns a Set view of the mappings contained in this map.




